## App Router Patterns (app/)

### Page Structure
- **Pages:** `page.tsx` files in route directories
- **Layouts:** `layout.tsx` files for shared layouts
- **Loading:** `loading.tsx` for loading states
- **Error:** `error.tsx` for error boundaries

### Route Organization
```
app/
├── admin/           # Admin dashboard (role: admin)
├── auth/            # Authentication pages (public)
├── client/          # Customer features (authenticated)
├── control_panel/   # Super admin panel (role: admin/super_admin)
└── api/             # API routes (NextAuth)
```

## Component Guidelines
- Use TypeScript interfaces from [types/index.ts](mdc:types/index.ts)
- Follow established prop patterns (ButtonProps, InputProps, etc.)
- Support both authenticated and guest users where applicable
- Use consistent styling with Tailwind CSS classes
- Implement proper error handling and loading states
- Maintain mobile-first responsive design